Date: 15/2/1894
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: Our Ruahine plant is thus described by Sir J. D. Hooker:- "Aciphylla colensoi, stem 6ft to 9ft high. Leaves forming a circle 5ft to 6ft in diameter of bayonet-like spikes, 2ft long, pinnate; leaflets 8in to 10in long,  1/2in broad, very thick and coriaceous, narrow linear acuminate, &c .. They are apparently two varieties; both are called 'speargrass' and 'wild Spaniard.' "Handbook Flora, N.Z," p.92.
