Quote: Tussocks can hide some nasty plants, such as Spaniard, or speargrass. So called because of their stiff, rapier-sharp leaves that bristle in every direction, Spaniards are not shy about stabbing the unwary tramper, and make a painful seat if you choose to flop down in the wrong spot.
